<div class="c240_22"> 
<div id="v240.22.1"><span class="H8034 s">A <i>good</i> name</span><span class="H977 s"> <i>is</i> rather to be chosen</span><span class="H7227 s"> than great</span><span class="H6239 s"> riches</span><span class="H2896 s">, <i>and</i> loving</span><span class="H2580 s"> favour</span><span class="H3701 s"> rather than silver</span><span class="H2091 s"> and gold</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (loving…: or, favour is better than, etc)</span></div> 
<div id="v240.22.2"><span class="H6223 s">The rich</span><span class="H7326 s"> and poor</span><span class="H6298 s"> meet together</span><span class="H3068 s">: the LORD</span><span class="H6213 s"> <i>is</i> the maker</span> of them all.</div> 
<div id="v240.22.3"><span class="H6175 s">A prudent</span><span class="H7200 s"> <i>man</i> foreseeth</span><span class="H7451 s"> the evil</span><span class="H5641 s">, and hideth</span><span class="H5641 s"> †</span><span class="H6612 s"> himself: but the simple</span><span class="H5674 s"> pass on</span><span class="H6064 s">, and are punished</span>.</div> 
<div id="v240.22.4"><span class="H6118 s">By</span><span class="H6038 s"> humility</span><span class="H3374 s"> <i>and</i> the fear</span><span class="H3068 s"> of the LORD</span><span class="H6239 s"> <i>are</i> riches</span><span class="H3519 s">, and honour</span><span class="H2416 s">, and life</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (By…: or, The reward of humility, etc)</span></div> 
<div id="v240.22.5"><span class="H6791 s">Thorns</span><span class="H6341 s"> <i>and</i> snares</span><span class="H1870 s"> <i>are</i> in the way</span><span class="H6141 s"> of the froward</span><span class="H8104 s">: he that doth keep</span><span class="H5315 s"> his soul</span><span class="H7368 s"> shall be far</span> from them.</div> 
<div id="v240.22.6"><span class="H2596 s">Train up</span><span class="H5288 s"> a child</span><span class="H1870 s"> in the way</span><span class="H6310 s"> he should go</span><span class="H2204 s">: and when he is old</span><span class="H5493 s">, he will not depart</span> from it. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Train…: or, Catechise) (in…: Heb. in his way)</span></div> 
<div id="v240.22.7"><span class="H6223 s">The rich</span><span class="H4910 s"> ruleth</span><span class="H7326 s"> over the poor</span><span class="H3867 s">, and the borrower</span><span class="H5650 s"> <i>is</i> servant</span><span class="H376 s"> to the lender</span><span class="H3867 s"> †</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (the lender: Heb. the man that lendeth)</span></div> 
<div id="v240.22.8"><span class="H2232 s">He that soweth</span><span class="H5766 s"> iniquity</span><span class="H7114 s"> shall reap</span><span class="H205 s"> vanity</span><span class="H7626 s">: and the rod</span><span class="H5678 s"> of his anger</span><span class="H3615 s"> shall fail</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (the rod…: or, with the rod of his anger he shall be consumed)</span></div> 
<div id="v240.22.9"><span class="H2896 s">He that hath a bountiful</span><span class="H5869 s"> eye</span><span class="H1288 s"> shall be blessed</span><span class="H5414 s">; for he giveth</span><span class="H3899 s"> of his bread</span><span class="H1800 s"> to the poor</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (He that…: Heb. Good of eye)</span></div> 
<div id="v240.22.10"><span class="H1644 s">Cast out</span><span class="H3887 s"> the scorner</span><span class="H4066 s">, and contention</span><span class="H3318 s"> shall go out</span><span class="H1779 s">; yea, strife</span><span class="H7036 s"> and reproach</span><span class="H7673 s"> shall cease</span>.</div> 
<div id="v240.22.11"><span class="H157 s">He that loveth</span><span class="H2890 s"> pureness</span><span class="H2889 s"> †</span><span class="H3820 s"> of heart</span><span class="H2580 s">, <i>for</i> the grace</span><span class="H8193 s"> of his lips</span><span class="H4428 s"> the king</span><span class="H7453 s"> <i>shall be</i> his friend</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (for…: or, and hath grace in his lips)</span></div> 
<div id="v240.22.12"><span class="H5869 s">The eyes</span><span class="H3068 s"> of the LORD</span><span class="H5341 s"> preserve</span><span class="H1847 s"> knowledge</span><span class="H5557 s">, and he overthroweth</span><span class="H1697 s"> the words</span><span class="H898 s"> of the transgressor</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (the words: or, the matters)</span></div> 
<div id="v240.22.13"><span class="H6102 s">The slothful</span><span class="H559 s"> <i>man</i> saith</span><span class="H738 s">, <i>There is</i> a lion</span><span class="H2351 s"> without</span><span class="H7523 s">, I shall be slain</span><span class="H8432 s"> in</span><span class="H7339 s"> the streets</span>.</div> 
<div id="v240.22.14"><span class="H6310 s">The mouth</span><span class="H2114 s"> of strange women</span><span class="H6013 s"> <i>is</i> a deep</span><span class="H7745 s"> pit</span><span class="H2194 s">: he that is abhorred</span><span class="H3068 s"> of the LORD</span><span class="H5307 s"> shall fall</span> therein.</div> 
<div id="v240.22.15"><span class="H200 s">Foolishness</span><span class="H7194 s"> <i>is</i> bound</span><span class="H3820 s"> in the heart</span><span class="H5288 s"> of a child</span><span class="H7626 s">; <i>but</i> the rod</span><span class="H4148 s"> of correction</span><span class="H7368 s"> shall drive it far</span> from him.</div> 
<div id="v240.22.16"><span class="H6231 s">He that oppresseth</span><span class="H1800 s"> the poor</span><span class="H7235 s"> to increase</span><span class="H5414 s"> his <i>riches, and</i> he that giveth</span><span class="H6223 s"> to the rich</span><span class="H4270 s">, <i>shall</i> surely <i>come</i> to want</span>.</div> 
<div id="v240.22.17"><span class="H5186 s">Bow down</span><span class="H241 s"> thine ear</span><span class="H8085 s">, and hear</span><span class="H1697 s"> the words</span><span class="H2450 s"> of the wise</span><span class="H7896 s">, and apply</span><span class="H3820 s"> thine heart</span><span class="H1847 s"> unto my knowledge</span>.</div> 
<div id="v240.22.18"><span class="H5273 s">For <i>it is</i> a pleasant thing</span><span class="H8104 s"> if thou keep</span><span class="H990 s"> them within</span><span class="H3162 s"> thee; they shall withal</span><span class="H3559 s"> be fitted</span><span class="H8193 s"> in thy lips</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (within…: Heb. in thy belly)</span></div> 
<div id="v240.22.19"><span class="H4009 s">That thy trust</span><span class="H3068 s"> may be in the LORD</span><span class="H3045 s">, I have made known</span><span class="H3117 s"> to thee this day</span>, even to thee. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (even…: or, trust thou also)</span></div> 
<div id="v240.22.20"><span class="H3789 s">Have not I written</span><span class="H8032 s"> to thee</span><span class="H7991 s"> excellent things</span><span class="H4156 s"> in counsels</span><span class="H1847 s"> and knowledge</span>,</div> 
<div id="v240.22.21"><span class="H3045 s">That I might make thee know</span><span class="H7189 s"> the certainty</span><span class="H561 s"> of the words</span><span class="H571 s"> of truth</span><span class="H7725 s">; that thou mightest answer</span><span class="H561 s"> the words</span><span class="H571 s"> of truth</span><span class="H7971 s"> to them that send</span> unto thee? <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (to them…: or, to those that send thee?)</span></div> 
<div id="v240.22.22"><span class="H1497 s">Rob</span><span class="H1800 s"> not the poor</span><span class="H1800 s">, because he <i>is</i> poor</span><span class="H1792 s">: neither oppress</span><span class="H6041 s"> the afflicted</span><span class="H8179 s"> in the gate</span>:</div> 
<div id="v240.22.23"><span class="H3068 s">For the LORD</span><span class="H7378 s"> will plead</span><span class="H7379 s"> their cause</span><span class="H6906 s">, and spoil</span><span class="H5315 s"> the soul</span><span class="H6906 s"> of those that spoiled</span> them.</div> 
<div id="v240.22.24"><span class="H7462 s">Make no friendship</span><span class="H639 s"> with an angry</span><span class="H1167 s"> man</span><span class="H2534 s">; and with a furious</span><span class="H376 s"> man</span><span class="H935 s"> thou shalt not go</span>:</div> 
<div id="v240.22.25"><span class="H502 s">Lest thou learn</span><span class="H734 s"> his ways</span><span class="H3947 s">, and get</span><span class="H4170 s"> a snare</span><span class="H5315 s"> to thy soul</span>.</div> 
<div id="v240.22.26"><span class="H8628 s">Be not thou <i>one</i> of them that strike</span><span class="H3709 s"> hands</span><span class="H6148 s">, <i>or</i> of them that are sureties</span><span class="H4859 s"> for debts</span>.</div> 
<div id="v240.22.27"><span class="H7999 s">If thou hast nothing to pay</span><span class="H3947 s">, why should he take away</span><span class="H4904 s"> thy bed</span> from under thee?</div> 
<div id="v240.22.28"><span class="H5253 s">Remove</span><span class="H5769 s"> not the ancient</span><span class="H1366 s"> landmark</span><span class="H1 s">, which thy fathers</span><span class="H6213 s"> have set</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (landmark: or, bound)</span></div> 
<div id="v240.22.29"><span class="H2372 s">Seest</span><span class="H376 s"> thou a man</span><span class="H4106 s"> diligent</span><span class="H4399 s"> in his business</span><span class="H3320 s">? he shall stand</span><span class="H6440 s"> before</span><span class="H4428 s"> kings</span><span class="H3320 s">; he shall not stand</span><span class="H6440 s"> before</span><span class="H2823 s"> mean</span> <i>men</i>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (mean…: Heb. obscure men)</span></div></div> 
